                subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d298">
                <note rend="inline" type="source">721.2315/180: Telegram</note>
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">The Ambassador in Peru</hi> (<persName type="from">
                        <hi rend="italic">Poindexter</hi>
                    </persName>) <hi rend="italic">to the <gloss type="to">Secretary of
                            State</gloss>
                    </hi>
                </head>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Lima</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1925-03-03T12:00:00-05:00">
                            <hi rend="italic">March 3, 1925—noon.</hi>
                        </date>
                        <lb/>[Received 12:48 p.m.]</dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>12. Your last cable. Peruvian Government promises to forward immediately
                    following modifications procès-verbal as substitute for Dr. Velarde’s proposed
                    statement: <quote rend="blockquote">
                        <p>“Dr. Velarde then stated that he was also authorized by his Government to
                            accept the friendly suggestion which the Secretary of State had just
                            made in the sense that his Government would immediately advise the
                            Peruvian Congress thereof—repeating at the same time its recommendation
                            that it approve the boundary treaty with Colombia.[”]</p>
                    </quote>
                </p>
                <p>Instructions in other respects to remain as previously given.</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">Poindexter</hi>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
    </text>
